reviews.review_text:
Under rated show ! Hey Gang,   I was at this show !  It was really, really hot and humid KY weather! I remember my dad telling me to be careful because the local police publicly said they were going to be in full undercover mode for criminal mischief.  As a consequence,  over 100 people were arrested during the event; I recall one article in the local newspaper saying bail was denied to one person because the license plate on their bus was "Rablin' Rose" ... wow !  

However, the Grateful Dead play a wonderful performance at this show.  I think for a couple of reasons , one they knew the cops were busting a lot of fans and the PA sounded absolutely horrible.  I heard a week later that the GD had problems with the local stage hands union and went to UPS for labor; my buddy who was working there got the job.  It seems to me when the police crack down on the scene; the band plays Truckin' ... yep , we get a rare for the time era "Space > Truckin"!  Also, the GD deliver a ungodly JAM off the end of He's Gone that no other show from the tour really touches it!  

A really nice LONG 1st set clocking into upwards of 80 minutes ; highlights are: Desolation Row, West LA fadeaway, Ramble On Rose (which seems always to be played in Louisville shows!) and Music Never Stopped!  The Second set is long too, highlights are China > Rider , Standing on the Moon, He's Gone > JAM !  , Truckin' - I think the China Cat is the best from the tour too.  
It was such hot weather, Garcia was wearing shorts - I also think I have a DSB because there is no tope flips in my source?  Also, check out View from the Vault #1 to see Standing on the Moon > He's Gone > JAM

I was there...wow what a day We drove down from Indy for this show and what a hot, humid day it was.  Beer sales were shut down right when the boys hit the stage.  We were allowed to take (2) one gallon jugs of water in with us.  Drop some paper about 45 mins before the show.  Beautiful long 1st set; I really enjoyed Peggy-O.  The second set was insane...the sequence of He's Gone - Drums-Space-Trucking-Wharf Raf-Going Down the Road...was freaky cool...The gigantic skeletons were dancing on the stage during Trucking.  Mickey pounding on the beam, producing sounds that I've never heard before. The cops were heavy handed throughout the day...saw a few people get busted.  Great show.  Sad to think Brent dead in just 3 weeks after this.
